<p class="p">Note that the multiplier (
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i47" class="math">
   <mo class="mo">±</mo>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>1.64) can be adjusted for different CIs as appropriate. For a special case 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i48" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">n</mi>
     <mn class="mn">1</mn>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mi class="mi">n</mi>
     <mn class="mn">2</mn>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mi class="mi">n</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, then 
 <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq1" class="xref">Eq. 
  <bold class="bold">1</bold>
 </xref> becomes 
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="i49" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Δ</mi>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">P</mi>
      <mn class="mn">0.9</mn>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mo class="mo">±</mo>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mn class="mn">1.64</mn>
       <mo class="mo">×</mo>
       <mi class="mi">σ</mi>
      </mrow>
      <msqrt class="msqrt">
       <mfrac class="mfrac">
        <mn class="mn">2</mn>
        <mi class="mi">n</mi>
       </mfrac>
      </msqrt>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>.
</p>
